    <div class="game-section">
      <h3>Settlement</h3>
      <p>After 18 holes, each player has accumulated a total point score. Settlement is based on the difference in points between players.</p>
      <p><strong>Example:</strong> After 18 holes, Alice has 58 points, Bob has 52, and Carol has 52. Total points across all players = 162 (9 × 18). The average is 54. Alice is +4 over average; Bob and Carol are −1 each. If the game is worth $1 per point, Alice wins $4, and Bob and Carol each owe $1 to Alice, plus $0 between themselves.</p>
      <p>Marker calculates and displays the full settlement automatically — no spreadsheet needed.</p>
    </div>

